    "ci_concept": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"ci-feature-shell\">\n  <section class=\"ci-section\">\n    <div class=\"ci-wrap\">\n      <div class=\"ci-section-head\">\n        <p class=\"ci-kicker\">The Concept</p>\n        <h2>Sound Shaped to Your Anatomy</h2>\n        <p>A Custom In-Ear Monitor is the most personal piece of audio equipment you will ever own. It begins with a silicone cast of your inner ear and ends with a sealed, hand-finished instrument that fits no one else. Between those two moments sits ten years of AAW craft — every shell unique, every voicing deliberate, every detail your own.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-article-body\">\n        <div class=\"ci-article-copy\">\n          <h3>An instrument, not an earphone</h3>\n          <p>A custom is not about volume — it is about belonging. A properly fitted CIEM nests into the concha, traces the contours of your ear canal beyond the second bend, and creates an acoustic chamber that is identical every single insertion. The mix you trust on stage tonight is the same mix you heard at soundcheck. The track that moved you yesterday will move you the same way tomorrow.</p>\n          <p>Performing musicians choose custom because the stage is unforgiving and a slipping seal costs them their performance. Audiophiles choose custom because they want the cleanest, most uncompromised path between recording and ear. Audio engineers choose custom because their craft demands a reference they can carry from studio to studio. What unites them is a single understanding: fit and sound are inseparable.</p>\n          <p>At AAW, every shell is 3D-modeled from a scan of your ear impressions, printed in medical-grade acrylic, and hand-polished to a smooth, bio-compatible finish. After a few minutes of wear, the monitor disappears — not because the music quiets, but because the object itself ceases to feel foreign. It simply becomes part of how you listen.</p>\n        </div>\n        <figure class=\"ci-article-figure\">\n          <img src=\"{{ 'canary-pro-ciem-pair.jpg' | asset_img_url: '1200x' }}\" alt=\"AAW Canary Pro custom IEM pair with transparent shells showing internal driver layout\" loading=\"lazy\">\n          <figcaption><b>Canary Pro custom pair</b><span>Transparent shells reveal the multi-driver architecture inside each earpiece.</span></figcaption>\n        </figure>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-subhead\">The three pillars of a custom monitor</div>\n      <div class=\"ci-pillar-strip\">\n        <div class=\"ci-pillar\">\n          <div class=\"ci-pillar-icon\">1</div>\n          <h4>The Impression</h4>\n          <p>An impression taken by an audiologist captures every curve of your canal, concha, and helix. A deep, clean cast — one that passes the second bend — is the foundation of a monitor that seals reliably and holds its place for hours of performance or quiet listening.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-pillar\">\n          <div class=\"ci-pillar-icon\">2</div>\n          <h4>The Shell</h4>\n          <p>Each shell is 3D-modeled to your exact geometry, printed in medical-grade acrylic, and hand-finished in our Singapore workshop. Inside that compact volume sits the drivers, crossover, and acoustic tubing — engineered to fit you, and only you.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-pillar\">\n          <div class=\"ci-pillar-icon\">3</div>\n          <h4>The Drivers</h4>\n          <p>Balanced armatures, dynamic drivers, electrostatic transducers, or hybrid configurations are precision-placed and connected through hand-tuned acoustic tubing. Each driver covers a defined band — summed by a passive crossover voiced by ear before it is validated by measurement.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
        "content_width": "large",
        "text_alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "primary",
        "top_space_desktop": 0,
