    "ci_science": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"ci-feature-shell\">\n  <section class=\"ci-section dark\">\n    <div class=\"ci-wrap\">\n      <div class=\"ci-section-head\">\n        <p class=\"ci-kicker\">The Science</p>\n        <h2>How Custom Monitors Work</h2>\n        <p>Four acoustic principles work in concert inside every AAW custom. Together they explain why a custom monitor sounds the way it does — and why it stays consistent in a way no universal alternative can quite match.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-article-body ci-grid-2 flip\">\n        <figure class=\"ci-article-figure\">\n          <img src=\"{{ 'halcyon-ciem-fit-7.jpg' | asset_img_url: '1200x' }}\" alt=\"AAW custom IEM faceplate detail showing the precision of hand-finished CIEM shells\" loading=\"lazy\">\n          <figcaption><b>Precision shell craft</b><span>Each shell is a sealed acoustic chamber. Wall thickness, nozzle bore, and driver geometry all shape the final voice — every detail decided before a single piece of acrylic is printed.</span></figcaption>\n        </figure>\n        <div class=\"ci-article-copy\">\n          <h3>Seal and isolation</h3>\n          <p>A custom forms a complete acoustic seal deep inside the ear canal. Where a silicone tip compresses unevenly and rebounds differently each session, a rigid acrylic shell sits at the same depth, every time. The result is passive isolation of up to 26 dB — enough to turn a 110 dB stage into a comfortable listening room without a single electronic component in the path.</p>\n          <h3>Driver configuration</h3>\n          <p>AAW customs are built around balanced armature, dynamic, and hybrid driver platforms. Balanced armatures move with surgical speed for detail and articulation. Dynamic drivers move air and deliver the physical weight of low frequencies. Multi-driver designs dedicate individual transducers to specific bands — sub-bass, mid-bass, midrange, treble, super-tweeter — each tuned to do one thing exceptionally well.</p>\n          <h3>Crossover and tubing</h3>\n          <p>A passive crossover splits the audio signal across the drivers; the length and diameter of the acoustic tubing between driver and nozzle complete the voicing. This interplay of electrical and acoustic filtering is what gives every AAW model its signature — warm and musical, neutral and revealing, or anything we tune in between. The choice is yours, and we honour it precisely.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
        "content_width": "large",
