    "ci_usecases": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"ci-feature-shell\">\n  <section class=\"ci-section dark\">\n    <div class=\"ci-wrap\">\n      <div class=\"ci-section-head\">\n        <p class=\"ci-kicker\">Use Cases</p>\n        <h2>Who Lives with Custom Monitors</h2>\n        <p>A custom is never just one thing. It is a tool for the working musician, a reference for the engineer, a private listening room for the audiophile. Each role calls on a different blend of isolation, accuracy, and comfort — and AAW has spent a decade refining all three.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-usecase-grid\">\n        <div class=\"ci-usecase-card\">\n          <h3>On Stage</h3>\n          <p>The original use case, and still the most demanding. A performing musician needs to hear their own instrument, the click, and the mix above a PA that can exceed 110 dB. An AAW custom delivers the isolation and resolution to monitor at a safe, musical volume — without disconnecting from the energy in the room. Vocalists, instrumentalists, drummers, keyboardists — they all trust the same craft.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-usecase-card\">\n          <h3>In the Listening Chair</h3>\n          <p>For the critical listener, a custom removes the variables. There is no tip-rolling, no seal inconsistency, no question of whether you are hearing the IEM or the fit. The driver sits at a known distance from the eardrum, the shell becomes a controlled acoustic chamber — and the recording arrives unfiltered, in the form the artist intended.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-usecase-card\">\n          <h3>In the Studio</h3>\n          <p>A reference monitor that sounds the same in a hotel room as it does in a mastering suite is invaluable. AAW customs are used by engineers to check mixes, evaluate masters, and make decisions they need to live with. The stereo image, the tonal balance, the depth of stage — none of them drift between sessions.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-usecase-card\">\n          <h3>In Daily Life</h3>\n          <p>Many of our customers will never set foot on a stage. They commute in absolute privacy, work surrounded by open offices without distraction, fly long-haul without compromising on what they hear. A custom is a long-term commitment to how you listen — and to how much of yourself you let the music meet.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
