    "ci_process": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"ci-feature-shell\">\n  <section class=\"ci-section dark\">\n    <div class=\"ci-wrap\">\n      <div class=\"ci-section-head\">\n        <p class=\"ci-kicker\">The Process</p>\n        <h2>From Impression to First Listen</h2>\n        <p>Building an AAW custom takes approximately two to four weeks from the day we receive your impressions. Here is the journey, step by step — quiet, considered, and never rushed.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-process-steps\">\n        <div class=\"ci-process-step\">\n          <div class=\"ci-step-num\">1</div>\n          <h4>Impression Scan</h4>\n          <p>Your physical impressions arrive at our lab and are 3D-scanned into our modeling software within one business day. We confirm receipt by email so you know exactly where your build stands.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-process-step\">\n          <div class=\"ci-step-num\">2</div>\n          <h4>Shell Design</h4>\n          <p>A technician models the shell around your driver layout, ensuring optimal internal volume and precise nozzle alignment. If you have chosen custom artwork, it is laid out and prepared for printing.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-process-step\">\n          <div class=\"ci-step-num\">3</div>\n          <h4>3D Printing</h4>\n          <p>Shell body and faceplate are printed in medical-grade acrylic. Support material is removed by hand and surfaces are polished to a smooth, bio-compatible finish ready for assembly.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-process-step\">\n          <div class=\"ci-step-num\">4</div>\n          <h4>Driver Assembly</h4>\n          <p>Drivers are placed, the crossover is soldered, and acoustic tubing is routed precisely to the nozzle. Every connection is inspected under magnification before the shell is sealed.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-process-step\">\n          <div class=\"ci-step-num\">5</div>\n          <h4>QC &amp; Listening</h4>\n          <p>Every pair is measured on our audio analyser for channel matching and frequency response. A final listening check, performed by a senior technician, confirms the monitor meets our tuning target before it is packed and dispatched.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-process-media\" aria-label=\"AAW custom monitor build imagery\">\n        <figure><img src=\"{{ 'aaw-ins-method-custom-group-2026-520.jpg' | asset_img_url: '1200x' }}\" alt=\"AAW custom in-ear monitors grouped after workshop finishing\" loading=\"lazy\"><figcaption>Finished Shells</figcaption></figure>\n        <figure><img src=\"{{ 'canary-pro-driver-render-clean.jpg' | asset_img_url: '1200x' }}\" alt=\"Rendered Canary Pro driver architecture for custom in-ear monitor design\" loading=\"lazy\"><figcaption>Driver Layout</figcaption></figure>\n        <figure><img src=\"{{ 'ciem-care-06-service.png' | asset_img_url: '1200x' }}\" alt=\"AAW service desk handling custom in-ear monitor care and refit support\" loading=\"lazy\"><figcaption>Service Support</figcaption></figure>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-subhead\">Universal vs Custom at a glance</div>\n      <div class=\"ci-compare-grid\">\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell header\"><h4>Feature</h4></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell header\"><h4>Universal IEM</h4></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell header\"><h4>Custom IEM</h4></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell label\"><span>Fit</span></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell\"><p>Standardised shape with interchangeable tips; fit varies by choice and ear anatomy</p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell highlight\"><p><b>Molded from your own impressions; intimate, identical fit every session</b></p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell label\"><span>Isolation</span></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell\"><p>Varies by tip material and seal quality; typically −15 to −20 dB</p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell highlight\"><p><b>Consistent full-shell seal; up to −26 dB of passive isolation</b></p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell label\"><span>Sound Consistency</span></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell\"><p>Insertion depth shifts with each wear, altering bass response and stereo image</p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell highlight\"><p><b>Fixed driver-to-eardrum distance; the same response, every time</b></p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell label\"><span>Comfort (3h+)</span></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell\"><p>Tips can press into the canal walls and fatigue over long sessions</p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell highlight\"><p><b>Weight distributed evenly across the concha; engineered for hours of wear</b></p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell label\"><span>Personalisation</span></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell\"><p>Limited to cables and tips; the shell remains standard</p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell highlight\"><p><b>Choose shell color, faceplate material, artwork, and engraving — yours alone</b></p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell label\"><span>Lead Time</span></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell\"><p>In stock; ships within days</p></div>\n        <div class=\"ci-compare-cell\"><p>Approximately 2–4 weeks from receipt of your impressions</p></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
