ion\",\n          \"name\": \"How is a custom IEM different from a universal IEM?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"A universal IEM uses a standard shell and interchangeable ear tips, so fit and insertion depth can vary. A custom IEM is molded to one listener's ears, giving a more consistent seal, repeatable sound, stronger passive isolation, and more room for shell and faceplate personalization.\"}\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Do I need ear impressions for an AAW custom monitor?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"Yes. AAW custom monitors begin with accurate physical ear impressions or approved digital ear scans. Good impressions capture the canal, concha, and outer ear detail needed for a secure seal and comfortable long-session fit.\"}\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"How much isolation can a custom in-ear monitor provide?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"A properly fitted full-shell custom monitor can provide up to about 26 dB of passive isolation, depending on the listener's anatomy, impression quality, and shell fit.\"}\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"How long does an AAW custom IEM build take?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"The page estimates approximately two to four weeks from the day AAW receives your impressions. The process includes impression scanning, shell design, 3D printing, driver assembly, quality control, measurement, and final listening checks.\"}\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Who should consider a custom in-ear monitor?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"Custom monitors are useful for performing musicians, audio engineers, audiophiles, and daily listeners who need stable fit, repeatable sound, passive isolation, and a personal shell design for long listening sessions.\"}\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Where are AAW custom monitors built?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"AAW custom monitors are designed, 3D-printed, assembled, finished, measured, and serviced from the AAW workshop and showroom at 76 Playfair Road, #01-03 LHK2 Building, Singapore 367996.\"}\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n</script>",
